 billed demurrage in full and the above calc is basis the same. In my opinion charterers are in a position to argue that laytime would not run for any of this waiting time. I have included a \u201Cworst case\u201D calculation to reflect this.\n\tRotation performed as expected, with differences as follows.\n-\tAn unplanned stop in Port Elizabeth for bunkers was required due to waiting time at load port and charterer\u2019s requirement for heating cargo (rebilled for $184k).\n-\tPort costs in line with estimates for load and discharge, but an additional $15k total was spent on bunker ports (Balboa and Port Elizabeth)\n-\tVadinar discharge completed in two parts with nearly one week between operations. Without load port deductions, demurrage claim is about $369k (13.7 days x $27kpd). Of this, about 9 days in jeopardy due to FM in Ecuador.\n-\tMGO Consumption much higher with additional days in port and aforementioned heating requirements.\n-\tVessel\u2019s HFO consumption was much better than expected, with about 8mt/day saved. This can likely be credited to the new hull paint applied in DD."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-04-12T21:05:53.7","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"4 Feb 06:01 - 13 Feb 09:42 in jeapardy due to FM (abt 9d 3h 41m)"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-04-04T15:26:00.473","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Increase $1.6k - Bunkers Updated"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-04-01T20:02:20.503","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Decrease $1.3k basis 50/50 laytime at load port"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-04-01T19:57:26.77","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Decrease $1.3k with estimated heating bunkers"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-02-25T17:52:27.64","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Increase \u002B$3k with estimated bunkers"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-02-09T20:35:07.82","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Increase $1,284 with estimated demurrage"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-01-24T17:53:34.617","modifiedByFull":"Ngunza, Jose","remar